  "doc_id": "4554",
  "text": "Coverage signal extraction Depth-of-coverage signals (i.e., the counts of reads overlapping a particular genomic position) were extracted from the alignments in a strand-specific manner and normalized by the total amount of mapped bases per data set in order to make them comparable among each other. The normalized coverage signals were also converted to the BigWig data format to enable manual data inspection in a genome browser. [CITATION_1] ",
